Haguichi is a graphical front-end to [[Hamachi]], a VPN tunneling engine. 

{{Note|Currently no ebuild exist for haguichi, therefore this article provides instructions on manually building and installing the package.}}

== Installation ==

== Kernel configuration ==

The kernel must support tunneling.

{{KernelBox|title=Enabling <var>CONFIG_TUN</var> in the kernel|
Device Drivers -->
   Network device support -->
      <*> Universal TUN/TAP device driver support
}}

=== Emerge ===

First unmask and emerge Hamachi, the VPN engine:

{{RootCmd|echo "net-misc/logmein-hamachi ~amd64" >> /etc/portage/package.accept_keywords}}

{{Emerge|net-misc/logmein-hamachi}}

Haguichi requires mono and gtk-sharp. Emerge them in one fell swoop: 

{{Emerge|dev-lang/mono dev-dotnet/gtk-sharp dev-dotnet/notify-sharp dev-dotnet/gconf-sharp dev-dotnet/ndesk-dbus dev-dotnet/ndesk-dbus-glib}}

Then nab the Haguichi tarball:

{{Cmd|<nowiki>wget http://launchpad.net/haguichi/1.0/1.0.20/+download/haguichi-1.0.20-clr4.0.tar.gz</nowiki>}}

Untar the file, and go into the resulting directory:

{{Cmd|tar -xf haguichi*.tar.gz && cd haguichi*}}

Then build and install the package:

{{Cmd|./configure --prefix{{=}}/usr && make && su -c 'make install'}}

